main event: An unknown object, presumed to be Russian, was reported trailing another unknown object over the Atlantic on 21 November 1953.
interesting points: The sighting involved 6 round visual observations,The objects were observed for approximately 30 minutes,Multiple conclusions included that it could be a balloon or an aircraft,The incident involved military equipment and was taken seriously by various branches of the military,No photographs were included with the report.
sighted object: unknown object presumed to be Russian
